headline: Will Major Partnerships Boost NextDecade’s (NEXT) Competitive Edge in LNG Development?
summary: In recent weeks, TotalEnergies announced a 10% stake in the joint venture developing Train 4 of NextDecade’s Rio Grande LNG project in Texas, while Baker Hughes secured a contract to supply main liquefaction equipment and ConocoPhillips signed long-term purchase agreements for LNG from the facility. headline: ConocoPhillips sends layoff notifications to some North Slope workers, part of global reduction
summary: Oct. 1—ConocoPhillips confirmed on Wednesday that it has begun sending layoff notices to some employees on Alaska's North Slope as part of its global workforce reduction. The company, Alaska's leading oil producer, disclosed in September that it planned to lay off up to a quarter of its global workforce, or about 3,250 employees. The reductions come amid a period of relatively low oil prices ...
